Notices.NoticeContent: Online ISS information session required before registrationAll new international students are required to complete the International Student Services (ISS) Online Information Session before registering for classes. You will need your UW NetID and password to access the online ISS information session. After you arrive on campus, the International Student Services (ISS) must collect copies of your immigration documents.
Summer quarter begins Mon, June 23.
Estimated Registration DateYour estimated Period I Priority Registration Date for winter quarter is . Registration begins at 6:00 AM. View your Priority I Registration Date.

International Student Registration RequirementYou are not registered for winter quarter. You may take a vacation quarter and remain in the U.S. if you have completed three full-time consecutive quarters and will be registered full-time for the quarter following the vacation.If you are not eligible for a vacation, you must register for at least 12 credits by January 17, 2014 or contact the Office of International Student Services, 459 Schmitz Hall.

FERPAThe Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA) of 1974 protects the privacy of your education records. However, your directory information may be released unless you inform the Registrar's Office. For further details check the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act web site.

About Peer-to-Peer File-Sharing and Copyright InfringementUnder copyright law it is illegal to download or share copyrighted materials such as music or movies without the permission of the copyright owner. Your actions when downloading or sharing files are traceable and could result in a significant financial penalty to you. For more information, go to the Peer-to-Peer File-Sharing and Copyright Infringement page in the Student Guide.
